title: The Solicitors' Journal
additional-notes: This is a British publication. Its contents may still be copyrighted even without renewals or copyright notices, if they meet GATT copyright restoration requirements for works first published outside the US.

A 1986 renewal for the 1958 book 'Brief to Counsel' by Henry Cecil mentions that portions had been previously published in the Solicitors' Journal in issues dating from July 6 to August 30, 1958.  That renewal may cover those contributions.  In addition, Cecil filed renewals for specific articles in issues datring from August 2 through August 30, 1958.
